name: Ben & Jerry's Topped Tirumisu Ice Cream Tub 436ml
description: Ben & Jerry's Mascarpone ice cream with fudge swirls and shortbread pieces topped with espresso fudge chunks and chocolatey ganache. Layer after layer, this coffee-and-fudge delight delivers what you thought only an Italian restaurant could: a truly knock-your-socks-off tiramisu experience. Ben & Jerry’s Tiramisu Topped ice cream is a tiramisu sundae in a pint! Dig into the decadent chocolatey ganache topping, complete with espresso fudge chunks, then descend into the depths of mascarpone madness. Dodge shortbread piece after shortbread piece as you follow those fudge swirls into dessert nirvana. Maybe brush up on your Italian before you pop the lid because with every scoop, you’ll feel like you’re lounging in a Roman piazza, wiling away the afternoon sipping espresso and enjoying la Bella vita. The best part? No plane ticket required. Simply grab your favourite spoon and your adventure has begun with your new favourite frozen treat. Now that’s delizioso! Pair this flavour with your favourite espresso for an even more authentic international experience. And it gets even better! Ben & Jerry’s ice cream is made with non-GMO sourced ingredients, including Fairtrade Certified sugar, cocoa, coffee, and vanilla and eggs from cage-free hens. And it all comes in responsibly sourced packaging, for a frozen treat, you can feel good about.

name: Ben & Jerry’s Ice Cream Tub Chocolate Fudge Brownie 458 Ml
description: Ben & Jerry's Chocolate Fudge Brownie Ice Cream Tub features fudgy chunks of brownie goodness mixed into rich, dark chocolate ice cream. Sounds like a dream? At first, that’s all it was. Long ago, we were making brownie ice cream sandwiches for sale in grocery stores. Sometimes there would be broken pieces in the brownie delivery, and we’d nab them for flavour experiments. What would brownie pieces taste like in chocolate ice cream? Pretty good, as it turns out! That original experimental flavour eventually became the legendary ice cream concoction known as Chocolate Fudge Brownie. Meanwhile, Ben Cohen had met Bernie Glassman, the founder of Greyston Bakery, a Yonkers, New York, USA-based company with a mission to end poverty and give back to the community. Equally important, their brownies were just so darn good – after sampling some, Ben handwrote a note asking for two truckloads of brownie pieces. While we knew Greyston would be the ideal supplier for turning Chocolate Fudge Brownie into a flavour sold by the tub, getting the brownies to cooperate wasn’t easy. After about 25 batches of brownies and six months of work, the flavour finally debuted in 1991, and it’s been a hit ever since. Greyston Bakery, one of the largest social enterprises in the USA, continues to provide the brownies for this and all of our flavours. Like all Ben & Jerry’s ice creams, Chocolate Fudge Brownie is made with non-GMO-sourced ingredients and eggs from cage-free hens. Fairtrade-certified producers supply the cocoa and sugar, and our ice cream chills inside your freezer in responsibly sourced packaging. Why not also try Ben & Jerry’s Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough, surrounded with creamy vanilla ice cream, or The Tonight Dough caramel and chocolate ice cream?
